# EU Scarf Quality Control & Compliance Handbook for Exporters  
## 2026 Reference Edition for Scarves, Shawls, Wraps, and Neck Warmers

> **Scope:** This handbook applies to knitted and woven scarves, shawls, wraps, mufflers, and similar accessories intended for export to the European Union.  
> **Update Basis:** Compiled according to current EU regulations and commonly adopted commercial quality standards as of **April 2026**.  
> **Prepared by:** **Weave Essence Technical Team**

---

## Executive Summary

If you export scarves to the EU, the real risk is rarely just appearance. Most shipment problems happen in four places: **labeling**, **restricted substances**, **color fastness**, and **physical durability**. A scarf may look acceptable on the inspection table and still fail in the market because the pH is out of range, the azo dye test is positive, the pilling result drops below buyer expectation, or the care label is incomplete.

This handbook is built to be practical. You can use it as:

- a **factory QC inspection reference**
- a **supplier briefing document**
- an **attachment to purchase contracts**
- a **pre-shipment compliance checklist**
- an **internal sourcing and technical review guide**

The goal is simple: help manufacturers, sourcing teams, importers, and brand owners reduce compliance surprises before goods reach the EU border.

