## General Safety Requirements Under GPSR

The General Product Safety Regulation (EU 2023/988) creates a wider safety framework for consumer products sold in the EU. Scarves are not exempt just because they are “soft goods.”

| Item | Standard / Regulation | Requirement | Applicable Products |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Small Parts Safety** | EN 71-1 | No detachable parts that can be swallowed by children | Beads, sequins, buttons |
| **Drawstrings and Cords** | EN 14682:2014 | Prohibited in head/neck area for young children; waist/bottom exposed length ≤ 14 cm | Children’s scarves/accessories |
| **Flammability** | EN 14878 or 16 CFR 1610 | Burning rate ≤ 100 mm/s | All scarves; brushed/plush fabrics require attention |
| **Sharp Edges / Points** | EN 71-1 | No exposed sharp edges | Metal trims, zipper pullers |
| **Plastic Packaging Bags** | EN 71-1 | Thickness ≥ 0.038 mm or perforated | To reduce suffocation risk |

### Practical warning

The neck area is already a high-sensitivity zone from a product safety point of view.  
If you are producing for children, never assume that normal adult scarf design logic can simply be downsized.

