## Labeling and Product Information Requirements

This is one of the most overlooked areas in scarf exports.

| Item | Legal Basis | Requirement |
|---|---|---|
| **Fiber Content Label** | EU Regulation 1007/2011 | Fibers listed in descending order by weight; ≤ 5% may be labeled as “other fibers” |
| **Country of Origin** | EU Customs Code | “Made in China” or “Product of China” |
| **Care Label** | ISO 3758 | Standard textile care symbols in fixed sequence |
| **Manufacturer / Importer Information** | GPSR Article 19 | Name, registered trade name/trademark, postal address, electronic contact address |
| **Traceability Code** | GPSR Article 22 | Batch number, model number, or serial identifier |
| **Warnings / Safety Information** | GPSR Annex I | Included where relevant, such as “Keep away from fire” |

### Why labeling still causes shipment disputes

Factories often assume the product is “fine” if the fabric passes testing.  
But from the importer’s side, a wrong fiber declaration or incomplete traceability mark is not a minor typo — it is a compliance exposure.

