## REACH Restricted Substances Quick Reference

Below is a practical quick reference focused on substances that show up frequently in scarf-related supply chains.

| Substance / Group | Limit Requirement | Common Source |
|---|---|---|
| **DMF (Dimethyl Fumarate)** | ≤ 0.1 mg/kg | Anti-mold sachets, packaging inserts |
| **Phenol** | ≤ 50 mg/kg | Antibacterial finishes, packaging materials |
| **NPEO / NP** | ≤ 100 mg/kg | Detergents, dyeing auxiliaries |
| **Antimony** | ≤ 30 mg/kg in PET materials | Polyester catalyst residue |
| **SCCP / MCCP** | ≤ 0.15% | Flame-retardant finishes, coatings |
| **PFOA** | ≤ 0.025 mg/kg | Water-repellent finishes |
| **Lead** | ≤ 100 mg/kg in coatings/substrates | Pigments, stabilizers |
| **Cadmium** | ≤ 1.0 mg/kg in plastics/coatings | Pigments, stabilizers |

> **Important:** The REACH SVHC candidate list continues to grow and now includes more than **240 substances**. Suppliers should provide a current **RSL declaration of conformity**.

### Sourcing note

If a scarf includes:
- waterproof treatment
- foil print
- rubber print
- PU patch
- decorative plastic parts
- unusual packaging inserts

then the restricted substance review should be stricter from day one.

