## Common Quality Problems and Rejection Thresholds

The following table translates technical issues into practical shipment risk.

| Issue Type | Description | AQL 2.5 Treatment |
|---|---|---|
| **Fiber Content Mismatch** | Claimed cashmere or fiber content short by more than 3% | Critical defect; zero tolerance |
| **Color Variation** | ΔE > 3.0 against approved bulk standard | Major defect |
| **Severe Pilling** | ISO 12945-2 result below Grade 3 | Major defect |
| **Excessive Shrinkage** | Length shrinkage > 5% | Major defect |
| **Holes / Snags** | Any visible hole or long snag | Critical defect |
| **Stains / Oil Marks** | Visible and not removable | Major defect |
| **Odor** | Mold, chemical, fishy, or abnormal odor | Critical defect |
| **Labeling Errors** | Missing or incorrect fiber, origin, or care information | Major defect |
| **Fringe Shedding** | More than 5 yarns released after hand-combing 3 times | Major defect |

### Factory-side interpretation

These are not just “technical defects.”  
Each one ties directly to one of three commercial outcomes:
- customs/compliance trouble
- buyer rejection
- after-sales return risk

