## Glossary of Key Terms

### AQL 2.5
A commonly used acceptable quality level for inspection sampling. In practice, it defines the number of defects allowed before a lot is rejected.

### Direct Skin Contact
Products intended to sit directly against the skin for extended periods. These usually face tighter chemical and comfort-related expectations.

### REACH
The EU’s core framework for chemical registration, evaluation, authorization, and restriction. It affects dyes, finishes, trims, prints, coatings, and packaging-related materials.

### SVHC
Substances of Very High Concern under REACH. The candidate list is updated regularly and must be monitored over time.

### Pilling
The formation of small fiber balls on the fabric surface during wear or abrasion. One of the most common commercial complaints for scarves.

### ΔE
A numerical measurement of color difference. In QC practice, larger ΔE values indicate stronger visible deviation from approved standards.

### OEKO-TEX Standard 100
A third-party textile testing and certification scheme widely used by brands and importers to assess harmful substance limits.

### Traceability Code
A batch number, model number, or similar identifier used to connect finished goods to production and recall records.

### Color Fastness
The resistance of dyed fabric to rubbing, washing, perspiration, light, or water exposure without unacceptable staining or color change.

